# v0.9.1-rc.4

This is a release candidate. Back up your vrconfig.yml at `%AppData%\dev.slimevr.SlimeVR` before running.
Please report all bugs in our [Discord server](https://slimevr.dev/discord), in the appropriate forum post in `#beta-testing-forum`!

## Installation
* Download the new release below and extract it.
* Replace `slimevr.jar` and `slimevr.exe` in the install folder (`C:\Program Files (x86)\SlimeVR Server`)
* To run SlimeVR, use the shortcut from the start menu or desktop, or open the installation folder and launch slimevr.exe.

## What's Changed
* tauri should work now by @ImUrX in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/831 (…hopefully)


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/compare/v0.9.1-rc.3...v0.9.1-rc.4

__________

# v0.9.1-rc.3

This is a release candidate. Back up your vrconfig.yml at `%AppData%\dev.slimevr.SlimeVR` before running.
Please report all bugs in our [Discord server](https://slimevr.dev/discord), in the appropriate forum post in `#beta-testing-forum`!

## Installation
* Download the new release below and extract it.
* Replace `slimevr.jar` and `slimevr.exe` in the install folder (`C:\Program Files (x86)\SlimeVR Server`)
* To run SlimeVR, use the shortcut from the start menu or desktop, or open the installation folder and launch slimevr.exe.

## What's Changed
* Fix tauri 2 again by @ImUrX in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/827
* Fix receiving OSC by @Louka3000 in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/825
* Fix the offsets of arms from controllers by @Louka3000 in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/826
* Add FT232 Serial Chipset to the known list by @unlogisch04 in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/823
