__________

# v0.6.0

Please report all bugs in [Discord](https://slimevr.dev/discord) for now in the #support-forum forum! Please send all new GUI problems to #gui channel! Help and support for VRChat's OSCTrackers is in #vrchat-osctrackers channel.

## Use the installer to install or update!
It is recommended that you use an installer to install or update SlimeVR if you're on Windows. You can find it here:
* Windows web installer: https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Installer/releases/latest/download/slimevr_web_installer.exe
* To run, open SlimeVR folder and launch slimevr.exe, or use shortcut from start menu or desktop

## Changelog since v0.5.1:
* **Added yaw drift compensation feature** that tries to compensate for drift after multiple resets. Useful for low-end IMUs, but almost no improvements to good IMUs or official slimes (@Louka3000, #436)
* **Tap detection and functionality improved and expanded with different taps and functions supported** (@Stermere, #375, #432)
* **Added support for Kotlin in the codebase** (@ImUrX, #401, #437)
* Added "Vive tracker emulation" "feature" (available in Development mode, (do not report bugs)) (@Stermere, #418)
* Improved support and CI for MacOS and Linux (@ImUrX, #412, #413)
* Improve CI by automatically generating version information from github branch and commit (@ImUrX, #351, #441)
* Window title changed to "SlimeVR" instead of "Slimevr UI" (@Louka3000, #441)
* Fix "I'm having trouble connecting" page not opening in the setup wizard (@macluxHD, #359)
* Basic workaround for using multiple sets on one network via config (@ButterscotchV, #383)
* Minor fixes and cleanup (@ImUrX, @Louka3000, @TheButlah)

### Translation changes
* **Use Fluent syntax for translations** that allow more complex translation conditions for better support of different langauges (@ImUrX, #414, #416, #419, #423, #447)
* Fix language selection menu not fitting on screen sometimes (@ImUrX, #406, #408)
* Added Twimoj font for language flags (@carl-anders, #377)
* **Added 🌎 Latin American Spanish translation** (@MaxEvil47, @Fowels, @ImUrX, #415, #425)
* **Added 🇮🇹 Italian translation** (@namakeingo, #382, #409)
* **Added 🇯🇵 Japanese translation** (@tamakiti3010, #374, #426)
* **Added 🇪🇪 Estonian translation** (@muumif, #452)
* Improved 🇫🇷 French translation (@Louka3000, HeySora #402) 
* Improved 🇻🇳 Vietnamese translation (@MenacingExiler, @TheDevMinerTV , #448, #407)
* Improved 🇧🇷 Brazilian Portuguese translation (@Gaabbu, #376, #429)
* Improved 🇰🇷 Korean translation (@Kamilake, #391)
* Improved 🇨🇳 Chinese translation (@Disappear9, @Naexen, #403, #410)
* Improved 🇵🇱 Polish translation (@Yexoo, #387)
* Minor changes to keys and tl system (@ImUrX, @Louka3000, #417, #419, #444, #451)

Huge thanks to translation contributors! If you wish to contribute fixes or new languages, feel free to create a PR. Currently we coordinate translations via our Discord server, you can check the general translation forum thread here: https://discord.com/channels/817184208525983775/1050413434249949235 or threads near it for specific languages.

## New Contributors
* @macluxHD made their first contribution in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/359
* @tamakiti3010 made their first contribution in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/374
* @namakeingo made their first contribution in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/382
* @Disappear9 made their first contribution in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/403
* @Naexen made their first contribution in https://github.com/SlimeVR/SlimeVR-Server/pull/410
